Information about VLC media player

WORKING OF VLC

VLC media player (commonly known as VLC) is a free and open-source, 

portable, cross-platform media playerand streaming media server 

developed by the VideoLAN project. VLC is available for desktop 

operating systemsand mobile platforms, such as Android, iOS, Tizen, 

Windows 10 Mobile and Windows Phone. VLC is also available on digital 

distribution platforms such as Apple's App Store, Google Play and 

Microsoft Store.

ADVANTAGE

1: VLC takes least amount of processing memory.

2: VLC is faster inand loading and good for technical experts.

3: it can be operate in windows,android ,mac ios,linux etc.

DISADVANTAGE

1: VLC does not rip CD.

2: VLC does not support real format.

3: The VLC media player play most codec's pack needed MPEG-2,MPEG-

4,H.264,MKV etc.

CONCLUSION

1:VLC media player is playing quite important role in modern life.

2: it will help to minimize data usage.

3: VLC has several meda player filter to edit video and it is quite 

easy
